<h2>Questions We Get on These Calls</h2>

<h3>How do I know if it's the bearing or the drum rollers?</h3>
<p>Listen to the sound. Worn rollers squeak or squeal — high-pitched and rhythmic. A worn bearing grinds or rumbles — deeper, more constant, sometimes metallic. Then check: open the door and push the drum gently toward the back. If it has noticeable play and moves when it shouldn't, the rear bearing is worn. We can often narrow it down over the phone based on your description — call us at (323) 990-7550 and describe what you're hearing.</p>

<h3>Can I keep using the dryer while it's grinding?</h3>
<p>We'd strongly recommend against it. The bearing wears faster the longer it runs degraded. Once the drum starts dragging on the rear bulkhead, you risk drum damage on top of the bearing replacement. A $320 repair today can become $600+ after a few more months of running it.</p>

<h3>Do you service all LG dryer models?</h3>
<p>Yes — DLGX, DLEX, DLE, DLG, and LG Signature series, both gas and electric. We carry bearing assemblies for the most common models and can source specific parts for less common variants. Give us your model number when you call and we'll confirm availability before we arrive.</p>

<h3>What causes LG dryer drum bearings to fail?</h3>
<p>Normal wear is the primary cause — bearings typically last 8–12 years under normal use. Overloading the dryer accelerates wear because the bearing carries more weight every rotation. Lint buildup that raises operating temperature also shortens bearing life. On machines over 10 years old, bearing failure is expected wear, not a defect.</p>

<h3>How long does drum bearing replacement take?</h3>
<p>Usually 90–120 minutes on-site. It's a full disassembly job — the drum comes completely out. We run a full test cycle before we leave and confirm the noise is completely gone.</p>

<h3>Is it worth replacing the bearing on an older LG dryer?</h3>
<p>On a 6–9 year old machine otherwise in good shape, yes — $320–400 makes clear sense compared to $800+ for a new dryer. On a 12+ year old machine with multiple failing components, we'll give you an honest assessment on-site and let you decide.</p>

<h3>Can you come today?</h3>
<p>Yes — call (323) 990-7550. Same-day service across Los Angeles County, Orange County, and Ventura County, typically 2–4 hours from your call.</p>

